HELP XT_NEW_ARGS                                        Steve Knight, Oct 93
                                                        SIREN Project

    xt_new_args( PARENT, [NAME], BINDING1, ..., BINDINGn, [MANAGED] )
        -> ( NAME, PARENT, ARGLIST, MANAGED )

This procedure is used for processing optional argument for widget
creation routines.  The PARENT is the parent widget.  NAME is an optional
string parameter that is the instance name of the widget.  The bindings
are each 2-element vectors or lists of 2-element vectors.  MANAGED is
an optional boolean (default <true>) that specifies whether the widget
should be managed.

The returned ARGLIST is suitable as an argument to -XptArgList- or
-XptVaArgList-.
